dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Ravindra b Mustafizur Rahman 21 (20b 0x4 1x6 46m) SR: 105

dismissalComment.html: tiki-taka catch between Rahane and Ravindra at midwicket. Looks like a slightly slower ball, which is why Kohli has not got all on this pull, and Rahane takes the diving catch at deep midwicket and lobs it to Ravindra before sliding into the boundary cushions

dismissalText.commentary: Glenn Maxwell c †Dhoni b Chahar 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: CSK have come roaring back. Maxwell is gone for a golden duck. What a huge wicket. Short of a length, top of off or thereabouts, Maxwell looks to punch at it with an open face. The face is just too open. Edges it to Dhoni. Actually off the face of the bat. This game has turned on its head

dismissalText.commentary: Ruturaj Gaikwad c Green b Yash Dayal 15 (15b 3x4 0x6 19m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Edged and taken on the second attempt by Green at first slip. This is excellent bowling and also excellent captaincy from Faf to keep the slip in. Keeps it on a length but well outside off stump. Gaikwad gets forward reaching for the drive. He gets a thick edge and Green takes a fairly simple catch albeit on the second attempt. Important wicket for RCB

dismissalText.commentary: Ajinkya Rahane c Maxwell b Green 27 (19b 0x4 2x6 26m) SR: 142.1

dismissalComment.html: Excellent catch by Maxwell at square leg and Rahane's sprightly knock ends. Back of a length ball but the line was crucial here. It was outside off, which meant Rahane had to fetch it and he could not control his pull. Maxwell is a few steps in from the boundary. But he adjusts well, and takes a reverse-cupped catch over his head
